## Phase 6: ISO 15066 Safety Wrapper (5-6 days)

#### [NEW] [iso15066_wrapper.py](file:///Users/ayushpatel/Documents/FYP3/safety_bigym/safety_bigym/safety/iso15066_wrapper.py)

**SSM Configuration (not hardcoded):**
```python
@dataclass
class SSMConfig:
    T_reaction: float = 0.1    # Robot reaction time (s)
    a_max: float = 5.0         # Max braking decel (m/s²)
    C: float = 0.1             # Intrusion distance (m)
    v_h_max: float = 1.6       # Max human speed (m/s)
```

**PFL Configuration (ISO 15066 Annex A, quasi-static/transient split):**
```python
# Force in N, pressure in N/cm², area in m²
PFL_LIMITS = {
    # Region:         qs_force, tr_force, pressure, area (m²)
    'skull':         {'qs': 130, 'tr': 260, 'p': 130, 'area': 0.00050},
    'face':          {'qs': 65,  'tr': 130, 'p': 110, 'area': 0.00050},
    'neck':          {'qs': 145, 'tr': 290, 'p': 140, 'area': 0.00100},
    'back_shoulders':{'qs': 210, 'tr': 420, 'p': 170, 'area': 0.00200},
    'chest':         {'qs': 140, 'tr': 280, 'p': 120, 'area': 0.01000},
    'abdomen':       {'qs': 110, 'tr': 220, 'p': 110, 'area': 0.01000},
    'pelvis':        {'qs': 180, 'tr': 360, 'p': 180, 'area': 0.00500},
    'upper_arm':     {'qs': 150, 'tr': 300, 'p': 190, 'area': 0.00100},
    'forearm':       {'qs': 160, 'tr': 320, 'p': 180, 'area': 0.00100},
    'hand_palm':     {'qs': 140, 'tr': 280, 'p': 190, 'area': 0.00060},
    'hand_finger':   {'qs': 140, 'tr': 280, 'p': 300, 'area': 0.00010},  # 1 cm²
    'thigh':         {'qs': 220, 'tr': 440, 'p': 200, 'area': 0.00200},
    'shin':          {'qs': 220, 'tr': 440, 'p': 210, 'area': 0.00150},
}
```

**Applying limits based on contact type:**
```python
def check_pfl_violation(self, region: str, force: float, contact_type: str) -> bool:
    limits = PFL_LIMITS[region]
    threshold = limits['qs'] if contact_type == 'quasi_static' else limits['tr']
    return force > threshold
```

**Quasi-static vs Transient Detection:**
```python
def classify_contact(self, contact, human_geoms, robot_geoms, fixture_geoms):
    """
    Quasi-static: human part contacts BOTH robot AND fixture (clamping)
    Transient: human contacts robot only, or robot + non-fixture object
    """
    human_part = self._get_body_region(contact.geom1, contact.geom2)
    is_clamped = self._check_clamping(human_part, fixture_geoms)
    return 'quasi_static' if is_clamped else 'transient'
```

**Sub-step force capture with type-aware checking:**
```python
def step(self, action):
    max_forces = defaultdict(lambda: {'force': 0.0, 'type': 'transient'})
    
    for _ in range(self.n_substeps):
        mujoco.mj_step(self.model, self.data)
        
        for contact in self.data.contact:
            region = self._get_body_region(contact)
            force = self._get_contact_force(contact)
            ctype = self.classify_contact(contact, ...)
            
            if force > max_forces[region]['force']:
                max_forces[region] = {'force': force, 'type': ctype}
    
    violations = []
    for region, data in max_forces.items():
        if self.check_pfl_violation(region, data['force'], data['type']):
            violations.append((region, data['force'], data['type']))
    return violations
```

